gomodel:SYNGO_1826  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 7/6/2017 Pim\nFig.3: The extracellular domain of IL1RAPL1 interacts with that of PTPδ.\nFig.6: The IL1RAPL1/PTPδ complex recruits RhoGAP2 to synapses.\n\n- PTPδ is a presynaptic protein, IL1RAPL1 is a postsynaptic protein, the complex formation can be seen as a handshaking between synaptic compartment and is considered as a 'signal'. The term 'trans-synaptic signaling by trans-synaptic complex (GO:0099545)' was applied.\n- The role of PTPδ is not examined to the same extent as that of IL1RAPL1 int his paper. The application of the term 'trans-synaptic signaling by trans-synaptic complex (GO:0099545)' comes from the specificity of PTPδ as a presynaptic partner of IL1RAPL1 as shown in Fig.3.. Experimental description: Literal form M&M\n\"Cell culture, transfection, staining and quantification\nof primary rat hippocampal neurons\nLow-density hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared from E18-E19 rat hippocampi as previously described with minor modifications\"\n\n7/6/2017 Pim\n- Species of the over-expressed protein is traced back to **human** species via PMID:20139422. literal: \"PTPδ-ecto-pDis and PTPσ-ecto-pDis have been previously described (19)\"--> \"...human PTP-δ-Ecto (NM_002839, aa 21-1174), ... \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1826" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

